6. propulit is the reading justly preferred to that which has the best MSS. authority, protulit.

6. inscium, ‘yet unconscious ’. The early efforts of the bird are a matter of instinct only.

7. verni: the elder Scaliger (Julius Caesar, who must be distin· guished from his son Joseph, a far superior critic) objected that young eagles do not fly before August, and proposed vernis. As Page re- marks, “even by thus making the line intolerable he only gets to the beginning of summer’'. The criticism is preposterously absurd. Horace knew and cared nothing about the habits of young eagles.
